  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional 1-2 minutes, until fragrant.",
    "Add the tomato paste and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the shredded V\u00113terbottensost cheese and cook until melted and smooth.",
    "Stir in the chopped cilantro, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the red wine vinegar and beurre-monte, and stir until combined.",
    "Pour in the water and bring the mixture to a simmer.",
    "Reduce heat to low and cook, covered, for 20-25 minutes or until the cheese has thickened and the sauce has reduced slightly.",
    "Garnish with sliced scallions and serve over rice or with crusty bread."
